comments.body:
From libvirt docs:
{code}The target element controls the bus / device under which the disk is exposed to the guest OS. The dev attribute indicates the "logical" device name. The actual device name specified is not guaranteed to map to the device name in the guest OS. Treat it as a device ordering hint. {code}
Since device name is not guaranteed by libvirt I am wondering if Eucalyptus can add dummy devices for missing 'letters' on start up and detach them right after instance started? In the example above Eucalyptus could configure dummy entries for {{vdb}} and {{vdd}} and detach them later. Unfortunately this approach would not work for volumes attached after instance start.
